{
  "doc_id": "33732",
  "text": "A compact, low loss UWB microstrip filter has been designed and developed consisting of \"Butterfly\" shape quarter-wavelength shortcircuited stubs and connecting transmission lines, utilizing 45 • mitered bend, with less number of vias compared to quarter-wave length shortcircuited stubs filter reported in [CITATION_1] . The new pattern delivers better S-parameters and group delay than its previous model [CITATION_2] , with a compact size of 21 mm×14 mm, giving 30% size reduction. Equivalent circuit for the new filter has been extracted nicely.",
